//INSTALLATION GUIDE

1) Clone the repository
2) If you want his project cool. But if you want new drupal. Remove the drupal folder
3.1) You need to download drupal separately.
3.2) cd /var/www/html
3.3) curl -O https://ftp.drupal.org/files/projects/drupal-7.98.tar.gz
3.4) tar -xzf drupal-7.98.tar.gz
4) docker compose up -d to run the container
5) You will need to deal with the permission on your local machine and in the container
6) "Docker ps" command in the terminal shows the containers running
7) "Docker exec -it container_id sh" to go into container
8) "bash" to run the terminal in bash
9) change permissions as you go, look here https://www.drupal.org/docs/administering-a-drupal-site/security-in-drupal/securing-file-permissions-and-ownership
10) there is a permission manager script in /scripts cd to that and run ./drupal_fix_permissions.sh -u=root -p=/var/www/html
11) run this "sudo chown -R $USER:$USER drupal" in local give access to drupal folder to you
